"v.使高兴 【英】 v. 使高兴(to make cheerful,merry,or lively; to invigorate or stimulate; animate) 【考】 反义词：sadden(使悲 伤) 【记】 ex+hilar(高兴)+ate →出现高兴→使(人) 高兴 【同】 同根词：hilarious( 高兴的；愉快的) 【例】 I was exhilarated by her visit. v. 鼓舞(使精神振作和精力充沛) = stimulate; 使高兴 = elate 【记】ex出, hilar高兴－使人表现出高兴－使高兴ex出, hil = hill: 不上课了, 出去到小山上玩－使振奋, 高兴 【参】hilarious(adj 欢闹的; 高兴的); exhilaration(n 令人高兴; 愉快) 【反】sadden(v 使悲伤) 【记】ex + hilarious 高兴的，hilar 拼音：嗨啦，高兴的呼喊声 exhilarate (v.)  1530s, from Latin exhilaratus ""cheerful, merry,"" past participle of exhilarare ""gladden, cheer,"" from ex- ""thoroughly"" (see ex-) + hilarare ""make cheerful,"" from hilarus ""cheerful"" (see hilarity). Related: Exhilarated; exhilarating."
